us":"rejected","overageDisabledReason":"org_level_disabled","isUsingOverage":false},"uuid":"00cbcf4a-7aa8-484d-accd-817878d5447d","session_id":"8786ba63-3b1f-40d6-a311-8337c51d41e5"},{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017Pgz5pWvLn9MeJMRuFQoYc","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→id: TICKET-0257\n     3→title: \"BUG: status.py does not display effective config values (session_ceiling_usd not visible)\"\n     4→type: BUG\n     5→status: OPEN\n     6→priority: P2\n     7→owner: systems-programmer\n     8→created_by: qa-engineer\n     9→created_at: 2026-03-01\n    10→updated_at: 2026-03-01\n    11→milestone: \"T4\"\n    12→phase: \"Foundation\"\n    13→depends_on: [\"TICKET-0251\"]\n    14→blocks: []\n    15→tags: [orchestrator, status, config, bug, t4-foundation]\n    16→---\n    17→\n    18→## Summary\n    19→\n    20→`status.py` does not display effective configuration values. TICKET-0256 acceptance criterion\n    21→requires that `python orchestrator/status.py --instance M8` shows `session_ceiling_usd: 10`\n    22→when `config.local.json` contains `{\"budgets\": {\"session_ceiling_usd\": 10}}`. The command\n    23→produces no config output, making config layering unverifiable via CLI.\n    24→\n    25→TICKET-0251 implementation notes specified importing `load_config` from `instance_paths`, but\n    26→the merged implementation only imports `resolve_instance` and does not call or display config.\n    27→\n    28→---\n    29→\n    30→## Reproduction Steps\n    31→\n    32→1. Ensure `orchestrator/instances/M8/state.json` exists (run `start_milestone.py M8 --force`)\n    33→2. Create `orchestrator/config.local.json` with content: `{\"budgets\": {\"session_ceiling_usd\": 10}}`\n    34→3. Run: `python orchestrator/status.py --instance M8`\n    35→4. Observe the output\n    36→\n    37→---\n    38→\n    39→## Expected Behavior\n    40→\n    41→The status output should include the effective configuration values, showing:\n    42→- `session_ceiling_usd: 10` (from config.local.json override)\n    43→- All other config values at their defaults from `config.json`\n    44→\n    45→This makes config layering verifiable without requiring a Python REPL session.\n    46→\n    47→---\n    48→\n    49→## Actual Behavior\n    50→\n    51→`status.py` output shows only state values (status, milestone, phase, wave, cost, workers,\n    52→completed waves, retries). No config values are displayed. Sample output:\n    53→\n    54→```\n    55→==================================================\n    56→  Hammer Forge Studio — Orchestrator Status\n    57→==================================================\n    58→\n    59→  Instance:   M8\n    60→  Status:     PLANNING\n    61→  Milestone:  M8\n    62→  Phase:\n    63→  Wave:       0\n    64→  Started:    2026-03-01T21:14:58\n    65→  Total cost: $0.00\n    66→```\n    67→\n    68→---\n    69→\n    70→## Evidence\n    71→\n    72→- Confirmed via: `python orchestrator/status.py --instance M8` — no config section in output\n    73→- Confirmed config layering itself works: `load_config()` returns `session_ceiling_usd: 10`\n    74→  when `config.local.json` is present (verified via direct Python call in TICKET-0256 smoke test)\n    75→- `status.py` source confirms: only `resolve_instance` is imported; `load_config` is never called\n    76→\n    77→---\n    78→\n    79→## Impact\n    80→\n    81→P2 — Defect in expected behavior; workaround exists. The config layering mechanism works\n    82→correctly at the library level. Users can verify the effective config by importing\n    83→`instance_paths.load_config()` directly in Python, but there is no CLI-level visibility.\n    84→\n    85→---\n    86→\n    87→## Suggested Fix\n    88→\n    89→In `status.py`, import `load_config` from `instance_paths` and add a config section to\n    90→`_print_full_status()` that displays the effective merged config (or at least the `budgets`\n    91→section) when not in `--json` mode.\n    92→\n    93→---\n    94→\n    95→## Activity Log\n    96→\n    97→- 2026-03-01 [qa-engineer] Created — filed during TICKET-0256 integration smoke test; config\n    98→  layering display criterion failed against status.py output\n    99→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8786ba63-3b1f-40d6-a311-8337c51d41e5","uuid":"0c22fca6-597f-4888-8bbb-c67fb1a752f9","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"C:\\repos\\Hammer-Forge-Studio\\tickets\\T4\\TICKET-0257.md","content":"---\nid: TICKET-0257\ntitle: \"BUG: status.py does not display effective config values (session_ceiling_usd not visible)\"\ntype: BUG\nstatus: OPEN\npriority: P2\nowner: systems-programmer\ncreated_by: qa-engineer\ncreated_at: 2026-03-01\nupdated_at: 2026-03-01\nmilestone: \"T4\"\nphase: \"Foundation\"\ndepends_on: [\"TICKET-0251\"]\nblocks: []\ntags: [orchestrator, status, config, bug, t4-foundation]\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n`status.py` does not display effective configuration values. TICKET-0256 acceptance criterion\nrequires that `python orchestrator/status.py --instance M8` shows `session_ceiling_usd: 10`\nwhen `config.local.json` contains `{\"budgets\": {\"session_ceiling_usd\": 10}}`. The command\nproduces no config output, making config layering unverifiable via CLI.\n\nTICKET-0251 implementation notes specified importing `load_config` from `instance_paths`, but\nthe merged implementation only imports `resolve_instance` and does not call or display config.\n\n---\n\n## Reproduction Steps\n\n1. Ensure `orchestrator/instances/M8/state.json` exists (run `start_milestone.py M8 --force`)\n2. Create `orchestrator/config.local.json` with content: `{\"budgets\": {\"session_ceiling_usd\": 10}}`\n3. Run: `python orchestrator/status.py --instance M8`\n4. Observe the output\n\n---\n\n## Expected Behavior\n\nThe status output should include the effective configuration values, showing:\n- `session_ceiling_usd: 10` (from config.local.json override)\n- All other config values at their defaults from `config.json`\n\nThis makes config layering verifiable without requiring a Python REPL session.\n\n---\n\n## Actual Behavior\n\n`status.py` output shows only state values (status, milestone, phase, wave, cost, workers,\ncompleted waves, retries). No config values are displayed. Sample output:\n\n```\n==================================================\n  Hammer Forge Studio — Orchestrator Status\n==================================================\n\n  Instance:   M8\n  Status:     PLANNING\n  Milestone:  M8\n  Phase:\n  Wave:       0\n  Started:    2026-03-01T21:14:58\n  Total cost: $0.00\n```\n\n---\n\n## Evidence\n\n- Confirmed via: `python orchestrator/status.py --instance M8` — no config section in output\n- Confirmed config layering itself works: `load_config()` returns `session_ceiling_usd: 10`\n  when `config.local.json` is present (verified via direct Python call in TICKET-0256 smoke test)\n- `status.py` source confirms: only `resolve_instance` is imported; `load_config` is never called\n\n---\n\n## Impact\n\nP2 — Defect in expected behavior; workaround exists. The config layering mechanism works\ncorrectly at the library level. Users can verify the effective config by importing\n`instance_paths.load_config()` directly in Python, but there is no CLI-level visibility.\n\n---\n\n## Suggested Fix\n\nIn `status.py`, import `load_config` from `instance_paths` and add a config section to\n`_print_full_status()` that displays the effective merged config (or at least the `budgets`\nsection) when not in `--json` mode.\n\n---\n\n## Activity Log\n\n- 2026-03-01 [qa-engineer] Created — filed during TICKET-0256 integration smoke test; config\n  layering display criterion failed against status.py output\n","numLines":99,"startLine":1,"totalLines":99}}},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01QqrL6CDko8DJ2Gf78LTkWk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Cy8mMo3Dfj7wnvVncKFEsn","name":"Read","